eNCA speaks to JMPD spokesperson, Xolani Fihla. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG -  Four suspects have been arrested in Johannesburg in connection with human trafficking during a patrol by the Johannesburg Metro Police Department. READ: Alleged human traffickers in SA illegally Two suspects were arrested in the CBD and two others in Meredale, south of Johannesburg. eNCA speaks to JMPD spokesperson Xolani Fihla in the video above. 